original: Carlander, Henning Axel, fd. postmästare, Karlsborg, f. 14/1/81 i Malmö av postmäst. Axel C. o. Amelie Sjögren. G. 10 m. Agnes Egertz. Barn: Eva f. 11, g. m, lantmät. Bo Skärman, Kristianstad. — E. o. postexp. i östra distr. 99, e. bitr. i Finspång 00, i Mjölby 02 o. v. järnv:posten i östra distr. s. å., postexp. där 06, i Vingåker 09, Vimmerby 10-13, Norrköp. I 13-16, Vingåker 16-19, i Västervik 20-23, i mell. distr. 24, postassist. där 25, tf. förste posta&sist. i Norrtälje s. å., förste postassist. där 26, postmäst. i Karlsborg 28-46. Hobby: filateli. GMnr.
translated:
Carlander, Henning Axel, former postmaster, Karlsborg, born on January 14th, 1881 in Malmö to postmaster Axel C. and Amelie Sjögren. Married for 10 years to Agnes Egertz. They had a daughter named Eva, born in 1911, who married a surveyor named Bo Skärman from Kristianstad. 

He started working as a temporary postal clerk in the eastern district in 1899, became an assistant in Finspång in 1900, Mjölby in 1902 and joined the mail train in the eastern district in the same year. He was employed as a postal clerk there in 1906, in Vingåker in 1909, Vimmerby in 1910-1913, Norrköping in 1913-1916, Vingåker in 1916-1919, in Västervik in 1920-1923, in the central district in 1924, post assistant there in 1925, acting first postal assistant in Norrtälje the same year, first postal assistant there in 1926 and served as postmaster in Karlsborg from 1928-1946. His hobby was philately. GMnr. (no translation available)
